# AudioKit Development Guidelines

## Monorepo Structure

```
audiokit/
  apps/
    web/                  # Svelte frontend application
      src/               
      package.json
      tsconfig.json
      vite.config.ts
      tailwind.config.ts
  
  packages/
    audiokit/            # Python backend package
      audiokit/
        core.py         # Core audio processing
        db.py          # Database operations
        llm.py         # AI/ML functionality
        logger.py      # Logging utilities
        utils.py       # Helper functions
      tests/
      pyproject.toml
      poetry.lock
      README.md

  .cursorrules          # Development guidelines
  .env                  # Environment configuration
  justfile             # Command runner
  README.md            # Project documentation
```

## Core Technical Stack

### Frontend Framework (apps/web)

- Svelte 5 with Runes (REQUIRED)
- SvelteKit 2 for routing and server features
- TypeScript for all code
- Tailwind CSS with Shadcn UI components
- Paraglide.js for internationalization
- Vite for build tooling

### Backend Services (packages/audiokit)

- Python 3.11+ with Poetry for dependency management
- Core Dependencies:
  - spotipy: Spotify API integration
  - pydantic: Data validation and settings management
  - pandas: Data processing and analytics
  - matplotlib/seaborn: Visualization
  - fastapi: REST API framework
  - asyncpg: Async PostgreSQL interface
  - transformers: AI model integration

- FastAPI for API endpoints
- SQLAlchemy 2.0 for database operations
- Celery for background job processing
- Redis for caching and message queue
- Docker for containerization

## Svelte 5 Runes Guidelines

### State Management Patterns

```typescript
// Basic state management
let track = $state<Track>({
  id: '',
  title: '',
  artist: '',
  duration: 0
});

// Derived state
let totalStreams = $derived(
  releases.reduce((sum, release) => sum + release.streamCount, 0)
);

// Effects
$effect(() => {
  if (track.currentTime > 0) {
    trackPlaybackProgress(track.currentTime);
  }
});

// Props with TypeScript
interface ReleaseCardProps {
  release: Release;
  onPublish?: () => void;
}

let { release, onPublish } = $props<ReleaseCardProps>();

// Two-way binding
let audioFile = $bindable<File | null>(null);

// Debugging
$inspect(release.status);
```

### Core Data Structures

```typescript
interface Release {
  id: string;
  title: string;
  artist: string;
  type: 'Single' | 'EP' | 'Album';
  releaseDate: Date;
  artwork: string;
  tracks: Track[];
  status: 'draft' | 'pending' | 'processing' | 'live' | 'rejected';
  platforms: DistributionPlatform[];
}

interface Track {
  id: string;
  title: string;
  duration: number;
  audioFile: string;
  isrc?: string;
  lyrics?: string;
  credits: ArtistCredit[];
}

interface Artist {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  bio: string;
  profileImage: string;
  socialLinks: SocialLink[];
  releases: Release[];
  analytics: ArtistAnalytics;
}
```

## Project Structure

### Frontend Structure (apps/web)

```
src/
  lib/
    components/
      ui/              # Shadcn components
      releases/        # Release management
      analytics/       # Analytics dashboard
      events/         # Event management
      profiles/       # Artist profiles
    server/
      distribution/   # Distribution service
      analytics/      # Analytics processing
      payments/       # Payment processing
    stores/
      release-store.ts
      analytics-store.ts
      event-store.ts
    types/
      release.ts
      event.ts
      analytics.ts
    utils/
      audio-processing.ts
      validation.ts
  routes/
    (dashboard)/
      releases/
        +page.svelte
        +page.server.ts
      analytics/
      events/
    (auth)/
      login/
      register/
    +layout.svelte
    +error.svelte
```

### Backend Structure (packages/audiokit)

```python
# Core audio processing functionality
# core.py
class AudioProcessor:
    def process_track(self, track: Track) -> ProcessedTrack:
        """Process audio track for distribution."""
        pass

    def generate_waveform(self, audio_file: str) -> WaveformData:
        """Generate visual waveform data."""
        pass

# Database operations
# db.py
class DatabaseManager:
    def __init__(self, connection_string: str):
        """Initialize database connection."""
        pass

    async def store_track_metadata(self, track: Track):
        """Store track metadata in database."""
        pass

# AI/ML functionality
# llm.py
class MusicAI:
    def analyze_track(self, track: Track) -> TrackAnalysis:
        """Perform AI analysis on track."""
        pass

    def generate_description(self, track: Track) -> str:
        """Generate AI description for track."""
        pass
```

## Feature Implementation Guidelines

### 1. Distribution Service

```typescript
// +page.server.ts
export const actions = {
  submitRelease: async ({ request }) => {
    const data = await request.formData();
    
    // Validate release data
    const release = await validateRelease(data);
    
    // Process and distribute
    const job = await queue.add('distribute', {
      release,
      platforms: ['spotify', 'apple', 'amazon']
    });

    throw redirect(303, `/releases/${release.id}`);
  }
};
```

### 2. Analytics Dashboard

```typescript
// analytics-store.ts
class AnalyticsStore {
  data = $state<AnalyticsData>({
    streams: [],
    revenue: [],
    demographics: {}
  });

  timeRange = $state<'7d' | '30d' | '90d'>('30d');

  filteredData = $derived(
    filterAnalyticsByTimeRange(this.data, this.timeRange)
  );
}
```

### 3. Events Management

```typescript
interface Event {
  id: string;
  title: string;
  type: 'concert' | 'festival' | 'meetup' | 'release_party';
  date: Date;
  venue: Venue;
  ticketing: TicketingInfo;
  capacity: number;
  soldTickets: number;
  status: 'draft' | 'published' | 'cancelled' | 'completed';
}
```

## Performance Requirements

1. Audio Processing (Python)

- Chunked file uploads
- Metadata extraction and validation
- Waveform generation with optimized matplotlib
- FFmpeg transcoding
- Async processing with Celery

2. Analytics (Python + TypeScript)

- Real-time metrics via WebSocket
- Pandas for revenue calculations
- Audience demographics visualization
- Platform-specific stats aggregation

3. Content Delivery

- CDN integration
- Audio streaming optimization
- Image optimization
- Redis caching

## Security Guidelines

1. Authentication

- JWT with refresh tokens
- Role-based access control
- 2FA for sensitive operations

2. Data Protection

- AES-256 audio file encryption
- PCI-compliant payment processing
- GDPR compliance
- DRM for content protection

## Testing Requirements

1. Unit Tests

- Component testing
- Store testing
- Utility function testing

2. Integration Tests

- API endpoint testing
- Distribution flow testing
- Payment processing testing

3. E2E Tests

- Release submission flow
- Analytics dashboard
- Event management

